## Gotchas
WRONG: new Queue('name') in every file that enqueues
RIGHT: export const myQueue = new Queue('name', { connection }); // shared singleton
WHY: Each Queue instance creates a Redis connection. Shared instance reuses the connection.

WRONG: job.data without validation
RIGHT: const data = schema.parse(job.data)
WHY: Jobs can be enqueued from anywhere. Validate data shape at the worker to catch stale/malformed jobs.

[Add more WRONG/RIGHT/WHY blocks as you discover them.]

